x4freetext: Experiment performed using the Super-FN
Tandem Van de Graaf accelerator of the J.D.Fox
Laboratory at the Florida State University
Natural carbon target with a thickness of 100 mu-g/cm2
Charged particles were measured using
two dE-E telescopes consisting of 500 mu-m dE
detector and 5 mm thick Si E detector, subtending an
opening angle of 0.25 deg.
Cross sections are weighted mean values of previous
measurements referenced in REL-REF and present
experiment.
Total uncertainty in absolute cross section
consisting of
1. uncertainty in elastic scattering XS
2. uncertainty from angle setting

measurements given in REL-REF and present experiment.
Detailed description of sources of uncertainties
are not given.
